"}, {"id": 3983786342, "node_id": "LA_kwDOAAsO6M7tc8Fm", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-strict-provenance", "name": "A-strict-provenance", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Strict provenance for raw pointers"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2022-05-26T09:46:58Z", "updated_at": "2022-06-08T10:24:12Z", "closed_at": "2022-06-08T10:24:12Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The pointer to integer cast has an implicit side effect of exposing the provenance, so it cannot be removed under strict provenance model.\r\n\r\nExample of an incorrect transformation:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\npub fn expose_addr<T>(a: &T) {\r\n    a as *const T as usize;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n-// MIR for `expose_addr` before SimplifyLocals\r\n+// MIR for `expose_addr` after SimplifyLocals\r\n \r\n fn expose_addr(_1: &T) -> () {\r\n     debug a => _1;                       // in scope 0 at a.rs:1:23: 1:24\r\n     let mut _0: ();                      // return place in scope 0 at a.rs:1:30: 1:30\r\n-    let _2: usize;                       // in scope 0 at a.rs:2:5: 2:27\r\n-    let mut _3: *const T;                // in scope 0 at a.rs:2:5: 2:18\r\n \r\n     bb0: {\r\n-        _3 = &raw const (*_1);           // scope 0 at a.rs:2:5: 2:6\r\n-        _2 = move _3 as usize (Misc);    // scope 0 at a.rs:2:5: 2:27\r\n         return;                          // scope 0 at a.rs:3:2: 3:2\r\n     }\r\n }\r\n```\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://